<h3 id=3D"CommunicationTheory-=E2=9C=85Summary.4">=E2=9C=85 <strong>Summary=
</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Pulse modulation</strong> converts analog signals into <strong>p=
ulse/digital forms</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>PAM</strong> =E2=86=92 analog amplitude pulses</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>PCM</strong> =E2=86=92 digital binary representation</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>DM</strong> =E2=86=92 1-bit difference encoding</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>ADM</strong> =E2=86=92 adaptive DM for efficient transmission</p=
></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>I can also create a <strong>diagram showing PAM, PCM, DM, and ADM wavefo=
rm examples side by side</strong> for a clear visual comparison.</p>
